  m_text: "Prof. Martin Weier \u2014 Project Lead, Supportive QA Feedback\n\n\nAyman
    Laghlali  \u2014 Lead Animator, Lead Programmer, Sound Designer, Composer, QA
    Tester, 3D Modeler\r\nKai Ozki AKA K.O.Kai(n) \u2014 Lead Designer, Dialogue
    Writer, Voice Actor, 3D Modeler\r\nMarvin Wernli \u2014 3D Modeler, Asset Creator,
    Game Designer\nNabil Benazza \u2014 Supporting Programmer, 2D Artist\r\nYassin
    Bolahrir \u2014 Lead Programmer, Level Designer, QA Tester, 3D Modeler, Game
    Designer\n\n\nA heartfelt thanks to everyone who supported us with their feedback
    and advice during development.\r\n\n\nAll sound effects and music compositions
    were created by Ayman Laghlali.\n\n\n3D models and animations were created by
    Marvin Wernli, Yassin Bolahrir and Ayman Laghlali.\r\nConcept design and level
    design were contributed by Marvin Wernli and Yassin Bolahrir.\r\n\n\nThe game
    was primarily programmed by Ayman Laghlali and Yassin Bolahrir, with support
    from Kai Ozki and Nabil Benazza.\n\n\nTesting and bug-fixing were primarily handled
    by Yassin Bolahrir, with support from Ayman Laghlali, Marvin Wernli, and Prof.
    Martin Weier.\n\n\nUnity (Game Engine)\r\nBlender (3D Modeling)\r\nAdobe Photoshop
    (Textures and UI-Design)\r\nRider (Programming Environment)\r\n\n\nAll trademarks
    and content within this game are the property of their respective creators.\r\nThis
    game is currently non-commercial and free to play (for now!).\n\n\nWe extend
    our deepest gratitude to our families and friends for their patience, understanding,
    and support throughout the development of Koh's Wrath."
